AI Concept Documentation
1. Introduction to Artificial Intelligence (AI)

Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a branch of computer science that focuses on building systems capable of performing tasks that normally require human intelligence. These tasks include learning, reasoning, problem-solving, understanding language, recognizing images, and making decisions.

Examples of AI
Virtual assistants (Siri, Google Assistant, Alexa)
ChatGPT
Self-driving cars
Recommendation systems (Netflix, YouTube)
Face recognition systems
2. Types of Artificial Intelligence
2.1 Narrow AI (Weak AI)

Designed to perform a specific task.

Examples

Chatbots
Spam filters
Voice assistants
2.2 General AI (Strong AI)

AI that can perform any intellectual task that a human can do.

Status: Still under research and not yet achieved.

2.3 Super AI

AI that surpasses human intelligence in all areas.

Status: Theoretical concept.

3. Machine Learning (ML)

Machine Learning is a subset of AI that allows computers to learn from data without being explicitly programmed.

Types of Machine Learning
Supervised Learning

Uses labeled data.

Examples

Email spam detection
House price prediction
Unsupervised Learning

Uses unlabeled data.

Examples

Customer segmentation
Market basket analysis
Reinforcement Learning

The model learns through rewards and penalties.

Examples

Game-playing AI
Robotics
4. Deep Learning

Deep Learning is a subset of Machine Learning that uses Artificial Neural Networks with multiple layers.

Applications
Image Recognition
Speech Recognition
Language Translation
Autonomous Vehicles
5. Natural Language Processing (NLP)

NLP enables computers to understand and process human language.

Applications
ChatGPT
Google Translate
Text Summarization
Sentiment Analysis
6. Computer Vision

Computer Vision enables machines to understand and analyze images and videos.

Applications
Face Recognition
Medical Image Analysis
Object Detection
Self-driving Cars
7. Robotics

Robotics combines AI with mechanical systems to perform automated tasks.

Applications
Manufacturing
Healthcare
Warehouses
Space Exploration
